pH is an important factor which influence the selective detection of trace levels of sunset yellow dye [9]. The C-dots were influenced by the pH of the solution in detection of sunset yellow. The fluorescence intensity of C-dots varies between acidic (1.0) and alkaline (10.0) environment as shown in the Fig. 4
                           . The fluorescent data clarifies that fluorescence quenching (F0/F) increases with weak acidic medium (6.0) and thereafter falls off in the basic medium. This is due to different functional groups on the surface of CDs interacts with the dye molecule and helps in selective detection of target analyte [54]. Therefore; F0/F reflects CDs dependence upon reaction medium pH (Fig. 5
                           ).
